{# FinCEN 314(b) request boilerplate.

   Section 314(b) of the USA PATRIOT Act allows financial institutions
   (including VASPs registered as MSBs) to share information with each
   other for purposes of identifying and reporting on suspected money
   laundering or terrorist financing. The institutions must each be
   314(b)-registered with FinCEN.

   Required Jinja context:
     - case_id, generated_at
     - victim: name, jurisdiction
     - perpetrator: exchange_name, deposit_address, total_received_usd
     - investigator (carrying institution): name, organization,
       fincen_314b_id (the org's 314(b) registration number)
     - tx_evidence: list of {tx_hash, block_time, amount_usd, explorer_url}
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>FinCEN 314(b) Information Sharing Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">31 USC 5311 — 314(b) Sharing</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">USA PATRIOT Act § 314(b) Information Sharing Request</div>
    <h1>314(b) Request<br/>to {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Information-sharing request submitted pursuant to Section 314(b)
      of the USA PATRIOT Act (31 USC § 5311 et seq.) and 31 CFR
      § 1010.540. This request is between 314(b)-registered financial
      institutions for AML / CTF purposes only.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content">

<h2>1. Identification of Requesting Institution</h2>
<p>
{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
FinCEN 314(b) Registration Number:
<strong>{{ investigator.fincen_314b_id|default("[TODO: insert 314(b) ID]", true) }}</strong><br/>
Point of contact: {{ investigator.name }}, {{ investigator.email }}
</p>
<p>
The requesting institution certifies that this request is made in
good faith for purposes of identifying and reporting activity that
the institution suspects may involve the proceeds of one or more
specified unlawful activities ("SUAs") under 18 USC § 1956, or
terrorist activity, in accordance with 31 CFR § 1010.540.
</p>

<h2>2. Basis for Suspicion</h2>
<p>
On {{ incident_date }}, customer {{ victim.name }} ({{ victim.jurisdiction }}
resident) reported the misappropriation of digital assets totaling
approximately {{ total_loss_usd }} in U.S. dollar equivalent. Tracing
of the misappropriated funds, conducted using on-chain analysis
methods producing chain-of-custody-preserved evidence, established
that <strong>{{ perpetrator.total_received_usd }}</strong> of the
stolen proceeds were deposited at {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}
at the following address:
</p>
<p class="mono">{{ perpetrator.deposit_address }}</p>

<p>
The transfers giving rise to this request are summarized below.
Each transaction is independently verifiable on the public blockchain:
</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Tx Hash</th><th>Block Time (UTC)</th><th>USD Amount</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for tx in tx_evidence %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ tx.tx_hash }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.block_time }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.amount_usd }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>3. Information Requested</h2>
<p>Solely for AML / CTF analytical purposes, the requesting
institution respectfully asks that {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}
identify whether:</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    The deposit address shown above is associated with one of your
    customer accounts. (Yes / No, with no further detail required if
    the answer is No.)
  </li>
  <li>
    If yes, the customer's account remains active and what category
    of risk classification, if any, your compliance team has assigned
    to the account at the time of this request.
  </li>
  <li>
    Whether you have filed, or are in the process of filing, a
    Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) relating to this account or to
    inflows from the chain-of-custody-evidenced source transactions.
  </li>
  <li>
    Whether other transactions from related addresses or counterparties
    have produced activity your institution has independently flagged
    under your Bank Secrecy Act program.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>4. Use and Confidentiality of Response</h2>
<p>
Any information provided by {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }} in
response to this request will be used exclusively for the purpose
of identifying and reporting on the activity described above. The
response will not be disclosed to any third party except (i) law
enforcement, in connection with a SAR or other reporting obligation,
or (ii) as may be required by applicable law. Both institutions
acknowledge the safe-harbor protections at 31 USC § 5318(g)(3) for
disclosures made in good faith pursuant to Section 314(b).
</p>

<h2>5. Verification of 314(b) Status</h2>
<p>
Receiving institution may verify the requesting institution's
314(b) registration via FinCEN's secure portal. If the receiving
institution is not currently 314(b)-registered, this request shall
be deemed withdrawn upon written notice to the contact below.
</p>

<h2>6. Response</h2>
<p>
The requesting institution respectfully requests a response within
ten (10) business days of receipt of this letter. Responses should
be directed to:
</p>
<p>
{{ investigator.name }}<br/>
{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
{{ investigator.email }}<br/>
</p>

</section>
</body>
</html>
